The Chancaní Park and Reserve was created and fenced in 1986, and since, its vegetation has been protected from human disturbance ( Cabido & Pacha 2002 ). Vegetation in the reserve is dry xerophilous woodland. The canopy is discontinuous and ~ 15 m high, whereas the shrub stratum (~ 4 m high) is thorny, dense, and almost continuous (
Carranza et al . 1992
). The climate in the reserve is highly seasonal, with a pronounced dry season.
